Project Name: LIMEN

LIMEN is a premium-quality indie puzzle game centered on dimensions, not optical illusions.

This project should feel like a thoughtful journey rather than a traditional puzzle game.

==================================================
CORE PHILOSOPHY
==================================================

The player should never feel that they are solving puzzles with items.

Instead, they should feel that they are understanding the rules of dimensions.

The real challenge is changing perspective and understanding dimensional logic.

Items exist only to support dimensional mechanics.

Dimensions are always the main mechanic.

Optical illusions are only visual support.

Do NOT make this feel like an escape room.

Do NOT make this feel like a puzzle game based on finding keys.

Do NOT make puzzles based on trial and error.

Every puzzle should have a logical solution.

After solving a puzzle, the player should think:

"I already had the answer.
I simply didn't understand this dimension."

==================================================
GAME STYLE
==================================================

Minimalist.

Clean.

Philosophical.

Calm.

Elegant.

Premium indie atmosphere.

No unnecessary UI.

No excessive colors.

No flashy visual effects.

No cartoon feeling.

Everything should feel intentional.

==================================================
VISUAL STYLE
==================================================

Primary colors:

White
Black
Gray

Colors should almost never be decorative.

Colors exist only when they communicate information.

For example:

Red = danger

Green = activated

Blue = dimensional object

Purple = fourth-dimensional object

Yellow = observation or hint

Every other object should remain monochrome.

The world should feel quiet.

==================================================
GAMEPLAY
==================================================

Core mechanic:

Understanding dimensions.

Dimension progression:

0D
↓

1D
↓

2D
↓

3D
↓

4D

Each chapter introduces one new dimensional rule.

Every later chapter builds upon previous rules.

The player never forgets old mechanics.

==================================================
DIMENSIONS
==================================================

Chapter 0

Concept:
Existence.

Chapter 1

Concept:
One direction.

Chapter 2

Concept:
Plane.

Chapter 3

Concept:
Depth.

Chapter 4

Concept:
Hidden spatial axis.

==================================================
ITEMS
==================================================

Items are secondary mechanics.

Never build puzzles around collecting items.

Never create inventory.

Never create crafting.

Never create upgrades.

The player can carry only ONE object.

Items only exist inside their puzzle.

When the puzzle ends,
the item disappears.

Objects:

Cube

Key

Orb

Mirror

Nothing more unless absolutely necessary.

Items should support dimensional thinking,
not replace it.

==================================================
PUZZLES
==================================================

The game should contain approximately 45 puzzles.

Chapter 0
5 puzzles

Chapter 1
8 puzzles

Chapter 2
10 puzzles

Chapter 3
10 puzzles

Chapter 4
12 puzzles

Ending

Difficulty should gradually increase.

The hardest puzzles should combine previous dimensional mechanics.

==================================================
PLAYER EXPERIENCE
==================================================

The player should constantly ask:

"What rule am I missing?"

NOT

"Which item do I need?"

NOT

"What button should I press?"

The answer should almost always be:

"A different way of thinking."

==================================================
QUOTES
==================================================

Before every puzzle,
display one short philosophical sentence.

The sentence should also secretly hint at the solution.

The player should understand its true meaning only after solving the puzzle.

The opening should begin with:

...

The ending should also end with:

...

Every other quote ends with a period.

Do not generate generic motivational quotes.

Generate original quotes that fit LIMEN.

==================================================
AUDIO
==================================================

Minimal ambient music.

Soft piano.

Quiet electronic textures.

Long moments of silence.

Small sounds should feel meaningful.

==================================================
OVERALL GOAL
==================================================

Players should finish the game feeling that they learned a new way of thinking.

LIMEN should be remembered as:

"The dimension game."

Not:

"The illusion game."

Not:

"The item puzzle game."

The game should leave players with a sense of wonder, curiosity, and quiet satisfaction rather than excitement.
